docs.lead_paragraph: At the height of Hong Kong’s Covid restrictions, the government gave Nicole Kidman and several others a rare exemption from the weeks of hotel quarantine required for travelers so that they could film a series about the malaise of privileged expatriates.

headline.main: Amazon Filmed ‘Expats’ in Hong Kong, but People There Can’t Watch It

byline.original: By Tiffany May and Yan Zhuang

docs.abstract: Our TV critic on the joy and melancholy of “Northern Exposure.”
docs.snippet: Our TV critic on the joy and melancholy of “Northern Exposure.”
docs.lead_paragraph: “Northern Exposure” premiered on CBS in 1990. Over the next six years, it drew millions of viewers, won a raft of Emmys and adorned the cover of multiple issues of TV Guide. But despite its success decades ago, “Northern Exposure” wasn’t widely available on streaming platforms until recently. Our TV critic Margaret Lyons considers how being out of circulation affected the show’s legacy, and the joys of rediscovering this classic series.

headline.main: A Beloved ’90s TV Show Finally Comes to Streaming

docs.abstract: Amazon, Google, Microsoft and other tech companies have been on a layoff spree this month, with the latest cuts differing from last year’s mass reductions.

docs.lead_paragraph: Last year, Mark Zuckerberg declared 2023 to be a “year of efficiency.” His company, Meta, soon laid off a third of its employees. Amazon, Google and Microsoft also cut tens of thousands of workers.
